If the table has been created through the web UI and set mode for field `NULLABLE `, the `mode` in API will not be returned

Request:

```
GET https://www.googleapis.com/bigquery/v2/projects/test-project/datasets/test-dataset/tables/test-table?fields=schema&key={API_KEY}
```

Response:

```json
{
    "schema": {
        "fields": [{
            "name": "redate",
            "type": "TIMESTAMP"
        }, {
            "name": "bar",
            "type": "RECORD",
            "fields": [{
                "name": "foo",
                "type": "STRING"
            }]
        }]
    }
}
```

This patch allows to return [] in glob section:

```yaml
outputs:
  - id: "#indices"
    type: ["null",File]
    outputBinding:
      glob: |
          ${
            if (inputs.runMode == "genomeGenerate")
              return inputs.genomeDir+"/Genome";
            return [];
          }

```
actual output when [] is returned will be:
```json
[job 4399300496] Removing temporary directory /var/folders/hx/3qsmpl9s50zdmn49jb03l_tw0000gn/T/tmpxPlAIt
{
    "indices": null
}
```

## What do these changes do?
Moves a helper function out of variant generator - allows for usage in other schedulers (ie ones with suggestions where spec should be parsed outside the variant generator).

